[805.42067, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H                   ssh-ed25519,ecdsa-sha2-nistp256,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H                   ecdsa-sha2-nistp384,ecdsa-sha2-nistp521,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H                   sk-ssh-ed25519@openssh.com,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H                   sk-ecdsa-sha2-nistp256@openssh.com,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H                   rsa-sha2-512,rsa-sha2-256\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H             If the specified list begins with a ‘+’ character, then the specified\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H             algorithms will be appended to the default set instead of replacing\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H             them.  If the specified list begins with a ‘-’ character, then the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H             specified algorithms (including wildcards) will be removed from the de‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H             fault set instead of replacing them.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H\u001b[1;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H                   ssh-ed25519,ecdsa-sha2-nistp256,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H                   ecdsa-sha2-nistp384,ecdsa-sha2-nistp521,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H                   sk-ssh-ed25519@openssh.com,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H                   sk-ecds"]
[805.420743, "o", "a-sha2-nistp256@"]
[805.420972, "o", "openssh.com,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H                   rsa-sha2-512,rsa-sha2-256\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H             If the specified list begins with a ‘+’ character, then the specified\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H             algorithms will be appended to the default set instead of replacing\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H             them.  If the specified list begins with a ‘-’ character, then the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H             specified algorithms (including wildcards) will be removed from the de‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H             fault set instead of replacing them.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H...skipping...\r\n             certificate either from an \u001b[1m\u001b[7mIdentityFile\u001b[27m\u001b[0m directive or \u001b[1m-i\u001b[0m flag to ssh(1),\u001b[m\r\n             via ssh-agent(1), or via a \u001b[1mPKCS11Provider\u001b[0m or \u001b[1mSecurityKeyProvider\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             Arguments to \u001b[1mCertificateFile\u001b[0m may use the tilde syntax to refer to a\u001b[m\r\n             user's home directory, the tokens described in the \u001b[4mTOKENS\u001b[24m section and\u001b[m\r\n             environment variables as described in the \u001b["]
[805.421006, "o", "4mENVIRONMENT\u001b"]
[805.421068, "o", "[24m \u001b[4mVARIABLES\u001b[24m sec‐\u001b[m\r\n             tion.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             It is possible to have multiple certificate files specified in configu‐\u001b[m\r\n             ration files; these certificates will be tried in sequence.  Multiple\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[1mCertificateFile\u001b[0m directives will add to the list of certificates used\u001b[m\r\n             for authentication.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 204 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[806.529947, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[806.531232, "o", "...skipping...\r\n     \u001b[1m\u001b[7mIdentityFile\u001b[27m\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Specifies a file from which the user's DSA, ECDSA, authenticator-hosted\u001b[m\r\n             ECDSA, Ed25519, authenticator-hosted Ed25519 or RSA authentication\u001b[m\r\n             identity is read.  You can also specify a public key file to use the\u001b[m\r\n             corresponding private key that is loaded in ssh-agent(1) when the pri‐\u001b[m\r\n             vate key file is not present locally.  The default is \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_rsa\u001b[24m,\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_ecdsa\u001b[24m, \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_ecdsa_sk\u001b[24m, \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_ed25519\u001b[24m,\u001b[m\r\n             \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_ed25519_sk\u001b[24m and \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_dsa\u001b[24m.  Additionally, any identities\u001b[m\r\n             represented by the authentication agent will be used for authentication\u001b[m\r\n             unless \u001b[1mIdentitiesOnly\u001b[0m is set.  If no certificates have been explicitly\u001b[m\r\n             specified by \u001b[1mCertificateFile\u001b[0m, ssh(1) will try to load certificate in‐\u001b[m\r\n             formation from the filena"]
[806.531334, "o", "me obtained by appending \u001b[4m-cert.pub\u001b[24m to the path\u001b[m\r\n             of a specified \u001b[1m\u001b[7mIdentityFile\u001b[27m\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh_config(5) line 629 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
